<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FINE DOESN'T BOTHER SHAQ
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ The NBA took another $10,000 out of Shaquille O'Neal's
pocket Monday, but he hardly winced at the news. In fact, he
danced.
</P>
<P>
   ``I only got fined 10!'' he said in mock glee, then smiled and
did a little jig for the benefit of reporters.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal earned the dock in pay for calling officials ``(bleeping)
idiots'' after he fouled out of Thursday's win at Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't complain about the NBA tax,'' he said Monday. ``I
don't complain about FICA, I don't complain about income tax, I
don't complain about the NBA tax. It is what it is. What can you
do? Can't do nothing about it.''
</P>
<P>
   For those keeping score at home, that's $20,000 O'Neal has lost
this season to what he also termed ``The D.S. tax _ the David Stern
tax.'' He previously was fined by the commissioner's office for his
Nov. 10 melee with Houston's Charles Barkley.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if he got his money's worth or not,'' quipped
Lakers coach Phil Jackson, who paid his own $5,000 fine for
criticizing officials earlier this season.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson lightly chided reporters for ``baiting'' O'Neal into the
remarks, but said he's not worried about his center's attitude
toward officials.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've never seen Shaq really on the court berate an official.
He seems to keep that pretty much inside,'' Jackson said.
``Sometimes I wish he'd be more vocal with officials, on the court,
on the spot, when the call happens, if it's a bad call.... He keeps
that stuff inside, and sometimes I think it just bubbles up (after
the game), and I wish he would get rid of some of that emotion
while he's there (on the court).''
</P>
<P>
   Dribbles: Monday's game against the Boston Celtics was the next
to last to be played on the FleetCenter's old parquet floor. The
Celtics play their final game on the half-century-old floor
Wednesday, then unveil a new floor, a replica of the original, on
Jan. 3....
</P>
<P>
   Lakers forward Travis Knight became a father last Wednesday,
when his girlfriend gave birth to a 7-pound, 15-ounce, 19{-inch
girl, named Natasha. Knight, 25, said both mother and baby are
doing fine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
