<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION
</P>
<P>
   So specialty editors can focus on one day's budget, CoxNet
produces themed features budgets each day. Here is the schedule:
</P>
<P>
   Monday for Tuesday: Technology
</P>
<P>
   TODAY: Automotive, personal finance and home &AMP; garden
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday for Thursday: Food, CD reviews, video reviews
</P>
<P>
   Thursday for Friday: Movie reviews, travel, books and fashion
</P>
<P>
   Friday for Saturday: Religion and science &AMP; health
</P>
<P>
   In addition, separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports,
business and commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. An ETA is given if a
story will move after 8 p.m. Eastern.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   THE LAYOUT'S DONE FOR YOU: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are
available for purchase in paginated form:
http://nytsyn.com/syndicate/pageex
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the current week. This
layout is available tiday after 2 p.m. EST.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 1221 _ If, as some reports out of Detroit have it,
the Chevrolet Camaro is reaching the end of its road, it comes at a
time when the favorite of young and young-at-heart drivers is at a
pinnacle. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes
3-column color photo of 2000 Chevrolet Camaro SS and 1-column color
photo of car's interior dash.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 2000 Chevrolet Camaro SS.
</P>
<P>
   THE MECHANIC _ My enthusiasm for the workings of automotive
electronics does not extend to my use of household appliances. In
this domain, my psyche is a shambles. (Carter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column color photograph of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ Linda looks at Cadillac's efforts in the 24-hour
Le Mans race. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ Gift suggestions for the auto lover. (Carter,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE-DEVILLE _ Russ reviews 2000 Cadillac DeVille (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL FINANCE
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA _ Suppose you could pick an accomplished
mutual nager and concentrate your investment on his very
best stock selections. You can indeed take the first option by
picking from a growing number of mutual funds that invest in 30 or
fewer stocks. They are called focused funds, or concentrated funds,
and there are scores of them. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   ETOUR _ ATLANTA _ Chat with Roger Barnett, president and CEO of
Atlanta-based eTour on the occasion of completion of a second round
of funding for 25 million dollars. We've been following Roger since
he was a one man band at Internet World in 1998 and look at him
now. Cell phone, huge offices, NYC public relations firm, offices
in three states, and a slew of magazine covers. Still, people
aren't really quite sure what e-tour does. We try to explain.
(Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ETOUR-BOX _ What eTour is, how you sign up, how sites are
picked, how it makes money, who's funding it etc. etc. (Katz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   CIVIL-DIVORCE _ It's called collaborative divorce, and it means
that lawyers for both parties sign a contract promising not to go
to court, but to try to settle amicably. If there is no settlement,
the lawyers withdraw from the case. The concept, which binds the
lawyers through the agreement, was developed in 1996 by Stuart
Webb, a Minneapolis lawyer who tired of seeing clients pull each
other apart, especially during divorces. The object is to minimize
anger and save money by avoiding a prolonged court battle.
Initially, you eliminate ``the psychic satisfaction out of filing
for divorce,'' Kanouse said, but you also eliminate _ or at least
postpone _ the vitriolic war that can scar both the couple and any
children involved. (Susman, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SINGLE-BUT-HAPPY _ DAYTON, Ohio _ It's not quantity of dates
that does it. It's not money, or education, or even the boyfriend
or girlfriend of the moment. The single people who are happiest
with Dayton, Ohio, and with their lives, find these things: a
neighborhood where they have friends, not just vaguely familiar
faces; the time to follow their interests; and the energy to do it.
(Lee, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JESUS-APPEARANCE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Jesus Christ is
worshiped as the human incarnation of the son of God, and his
likeness has been reproduced for hundreds of years by thousands of
artists. But they've all been making it up. The Apostles were
assiduous in copying down Jesus' message, but no one bothered to
write about his appearance. We know some things he said, but not at
all how he sounded. And though Bible readers are given vague hints
about the visage of the Prince of Peace, even those are
contradictory. (Belkin, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PSYCHOLOGY-TODAY _ Dr. Hap Lecrone's weekly psychology column.
(Lecrone, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-LIBERTY _ Movie review: ``Liberty Heights,''
Baltimore-set drama. Grade: C. (Ringel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MOON _ Movie review: ``Man on the Moon'' with Jim Carrey
in a strong performance as Andy Kaufman with song by R.E.M. Grade:
A-. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-SUNDAY _ Movie review: ``Any Given Sunday,'' Oliver
Stone's pro football drama with Al Pacino. It's long. It's brutal.
Sometimes it's good. Grade: B-. (Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 19.
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   ORGANIZING _ Enough's enough. That realization alone made
Kimberly Harrison seek professional help. Harrison suffers from one
of today's most common addictions _ stuff. The excess of the '90s,
heaped by a lack of time for organizing it, has snowballed into an
avalanche of clutter that leaves homeowners like her chronically
frustrated. Retailers like The Container Store and Calif. closet
are among a growing number of storage businesses targeting the
time-pressed consumer's weakness for disarray. (Flanders/AHill,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Thursday, Dec. 23.
</P>
<P>
   DISHWASHER _ If you have a dishwasher, do you know where its
owner's manual is? As with any appliance, you can get the most out
of a dishwasher if you use it the way the manufacturer suggests.
But there are a few general rules that apply to just about every
brand. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 26. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ Lee May's gardening column is not available
this week.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
