<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY-Y2K (Washington) _ Social Security Commissioner
Kenneth Apfel tells the 44 million Americans receiving the
retirement benefit that their monthly checks will be there Jan. 3,
unaffected by any year 2000 computer problems. ``The people who
depend on us can rest assured that their payments will arrive on
time,'' he promises. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
