<P>
   COKE-STOCK _ ATLANTA _ Standard &AMP; Poor's said Tuesday that it
downgraded its ratings on Coca Cola Co.'s senior unsecured debt to
A+ from AA-. The ratings agency lowered other credit ratings on
Coca Cola as well. The agency also lowered long-term ratings for
Coca-Cola Enterprises Inc., Coca-Cola Amatil Ltd., Coca-Cola Amatil
New Zealand and Australia's Coca-Cola Amatil Pty Ltd. About $6.3
billion of total debt was outstanding at Coke and about $11.2
billion at CCE as of Sept. 30, 1999. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SUPERBOWL _ ATLANTA _ The Super Bowl Host Committee is expected
to announce three new local sponsors. About four more are expected
to be announced within the next couple of weeks. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   GENERALMILLS _General Mills could be on the hook for more than
$4 million in charitable contributions to breast cancer research if
other states follow a payment formula negotiated by Georgia.
(Mantius, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
