<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA _ Suppose you could pick an accomplished
mutual fund manager and concentrate your investment on his very
best stock selections. You can indeed take the first option by
picking from a growing number of mutual funds that invest in 30 or
fewer stocks. They are called focused funds, or concentrated funds,
and there are scores of them. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   ETOUR _ ATLANTA _ Chat with Roger Barnett, president and CEO of
Atlanta-based eTour on the occasion of completion of a second round
of funding for 25 million dollars. We've been following Roger since
he was a one man band at Internet World in 1998 and look at him
now. Cell phone, huge offices, NYC public relations firm, offices
in three states, and a slew of magazine covers. Still, people
aren't really quite sure what e-tour does. We try to explain.
(Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   w/ETOUR-BOX _ What eTour is, how you sign up, how sites are
picked, how it makes money, who's funding it etc. etc. (Katz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SONE _ S1 has closed on its acquisitions of two of its
competitors. the new company is the biggest in its market and is
starting to be fawned over by wall street. stock has almost doubled
since Thanksgiving. (Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   WEBMD _ WebMD has merged with Healtheon and the corporate
headquarters is allegedly in Atlanta. Just what is in Atlanta and
what is in California _ or someplace in between? (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   PRATT _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Pratt &AMP; Whitney will say today
what will happen to its localy space propulsion unit. We expect the
unit is staying, but at what cost to taxpayers? (Pounds, Palm Beach
Post).
</P>
