<SLUG> BC-RECIPECX-SF </SLUG>
 CHRON  
 German Christmas Cookies Evoke Heartfelt Holiday Memories  
 
 Recipe Correction 
<TEXT>
<P>
   An ingredient was left out of this recipe in last week's Food
section. Here is the corrected version.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; COENENS' CINNAMON STARS
</P>
<P>
   Ingredients:
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup unsalted butter, softened
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   11/2 tablespoons lemon zest (from about 1 large lemon) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  2 to 4 teaspoons cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon mace
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon allspice
</P>
<P>
   Large pinch salt
</P>
<P>
   2 extra-large egg yolks
</P>
<P>
   1 cup blanched almonds, finely ground
</P>
<P>
   1 cup walnuts, finely ground
</P>
<P>
   13/4 cups sifted flour
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup flour + 2 tablespoons sugar
</P>
<P>
   11/4 cups powdered sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons rum or orange juice
</P>
<P>
   Food coloring and colored sugar (optional)
</P>
<P>
   Cream butter in a large bowl until light. Gradually add sugar,
beating until light and fluffy. Beat in zest, cinnamon, mace,
allspice, salt and egg yolks. Fold in nuts and flour. Briefly knead
to form smooth dough. Shape into ball, flatten, wrap in wax paper;
refrigerate overnight.
</P>
<P>
   Cover a board with wax paper or parchment and sprinkle and
rolling pin with flour/sugar mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Divide dough into 3 parts and roll the first one to 1/8 inch
thickness. Cut out with star or other cookie cutters. Reroll
trimmings with second part of dough and cut and roll until dough is
used up.
</P>
<P>
   Using a thin spatula, carefully move cookies to ungreased baking
sheets covered with kitchen parchment. Bake at 350 degrees until
the cookies turn light brown at edges, 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool a
couple of minutes, then remove to racks.
</P>
<P>
   Mix powdered sugar with rum; adding water to make the mixture
spreadable. Add food coloring, if desired. Glaze cookies while
warm; sprinkle with colored sugar.
</P>
<P>
   When completely cool, store in airtight containers for at least
2 days and up to 10 days, or freeze up to a month. Makes 3-4 dozen.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PER COOKIE: &LR;   &LR; 100 calories, &LR;   &LR; 2 g protein, 10 g carbohydrate,
6 &LR;   &LR; g fat (2 g saturated), 17 mg cholesterol, 4 mg sodium. &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
