<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Dec. 22. you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
GAY (Washington) - Last week, John McCain collected $40,000 from a
fund-raiser sponsored by the Log Cabin Republicans, a gay GOP
group. But, in the same week, the Washington Blade called McCain an
``enigma,'' on gay issues, noting he was once keynote speaker to an
Oregon group that was condemning homosexuality as ``perverse.'' How
can we explain the apparent contradiction? And is McCain willing to
step in on behalf of reservist Steve May, who is about to get the
boot? By JEFF BARKR. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOMB (Phoenix) - Is fear multiplying in the masses? Each news story
about bomb materials being stolen or smuggled heightens our
awareness of the potential for terrorism on New Years Eve. Scores
of people say they're staying inside, in part out of fear of
calamity. We check in with Phoenix area police guarding big
parties, the airport, federal buildings, major private
corporations, and real people about the real _ and perceived _
threats of New Years Eve. What will security be like on Dec. 31?
What concerns does the FBI have about domestic terrorism around New
Years?
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
