<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Dec. 22 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Eddie Ibardolasa at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BKC-UCLA-MAINE (Kahuku, Hawaii) _ UCLA will face Maine in the Pearl
Harbor Classic at 3 p.m. 
By Jon Wilner. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-BELTRE (Los Angeles) _ Baseball refused to grant Los Angeles
Dodgers third baseman Adrian Beltre free agency, a move that will
certainly lead to a grievance from the players' association. The
Dodgers were fined $50,000 and ordered to pay Beltre $48,500. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-MODESTI-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Baseball's penalties against the
Dodgers should be just stiff enough to avoid many players declaring
free agency. 
By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
HKN-DUCKS-DEFENSE (Anaheim, Calif.) _ The Anaheim Mighty Ducks,
once considered one of the weakest defensive teams in the National
Hockey League, have turned things around this season. They rank
third in the league in goals allowed and have given up only four
goals in their current four-game winning streak and just 10 in
their last eight games (5-1-2). And they have come from 10 points
down to tie the Kings in points with 41. 
By Greg Christensen/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-LAKERNOTES (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles Lakers notebook. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
HKN-KINGSNOTES (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles Kings notebook. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 

