<P>
   BANKONE-MARKETPLACE (Chicago) _ John McCoy is stepping down
after 15 years as head of Bank One Corp. Verne Istock, the
president, was named acting chief executive pending a search for a
permanent chairman and CEO. McCoy was under fire for problems that
surfaced last summer involving slowing growth in the bank's First
USA credit-card unit. By David Barboza.
