<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sponsors added to Super Bowl 'Countdown' events
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Metro Atlanta Super Bowl XXXIV Host Committee
Tuesday announced three new additions to its sponsorship lineup.
</P>
<P>
   Southern Company, MVP.com and Saucony will sponsor Super
Bowl-related events. The Jan. 30 game is expected to attract more
than 100,000 visitors.
</P>
<P>
   Southern Company, will sponsor the host committee's ``Countdown
to Kickoff'' pre-gram event at the Georgia World Congress Center on
Super Bowl Sunday. The event is designed to thank sponsors,
corporate contributors and other organizations that have supported
bringing the game to Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Newly formed MVP.com of Chicago will join RCA in sponsoring the
Super Bowl kick-off luncheon featuring NFL Commissioner Paul
Tagliabue, MVP John Elway, former Denver Broncos quarterback, and
others.
</P>
<P>
   The luncheon, which is open to the public, will be held Jan. 27
at the Georgia World Congress Centers. Tables are $1,000 and
tickets are $100 each.
</P>
<P>
   Additionally, footwear-maker Saucony will sponsor the Saucony
Super Run 5K through Midtown on Jan. 29. Those interested in
running can register at Just for Feet stores.
</P>
<P>
   Additional sponsors are expected to be announced within the next
few weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Recently, the host committee announced AutoNation USA, The
Coca-Cola Co., Progressive Auto Insurance, RCA and JCB Inc. as host
committee sponsors.
</P>
<P>
   Shelia M. Poole writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
