country of 22 million people, bigger than most of its Eastern
European neighbors, is going through harder times than most of
them. Ten years after the overthrow of the Ceausescu dictatorship,
on Dec. 22, 1989, freedom is here but prosperity is not. By Donald
G. McNeil Jr. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
