<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Dec. 22 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact the
Daily News, (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   KAJIMA-BELMONT (Los Angeles) -- Seeking millions of dollars in
upaid bills, the former lead developer of the Belmont Learning
Center has declared the Los Angeles Unified School District in
default of the building agreement for the nation's costliest high
school. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
wire.)
</P>
<P>
   NOGIFTS-GRINCH (Los Angeles) -- Bah humbug! Grinch burglars
broke into North Hollywood homeless shelter and stole about $1,000
in donated baby toys from the L.A. Family Housing Corp. Valley
Shelter. The North Hollywood cops were playing secret Santa Tuesday
trying to replace the gifts as they investigated the heist last
week. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move on the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news wires.)
</P>
<P>
   TREES-FIRE (Los Angeles) -- The Los Angeles Police Department
was cited by firefighters for keeping six Christmas trees that had
become fire hazards because they were so dried out. With Los
Angeles enduring one of the driest winters on record, people who
bought Christmas trees shortly after Thanksgiving are finding them
so dried out they are throwing them out. By Phillip Browne. (Will
move on the ``n'' California news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   DEGREE-CAREER (Los Angeles) _ Want a better career? Experts in
the education field sayt the key to earning a degree while working
full time is time management. By Suzie St. John. (Will move on the
``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
