<P>
   (NYT43) UNDATED -- Dec. 21, 1999 -- INSIDER-TRADING -- Federal
prosecutors in Manhattan on Tuesday charged the former chairman of
the bank Keefe, Bruyette &AMP; Woods, James McDermott, with insider
trading in a bizarre case in which he was accused of leaking
information about potential billion-dollar bank deals to an
X-rated-movie actress he was dating. McDermott, 48, is not accused
of making any illegal profits himself. (The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT42) UNDATED -- Dec. 21, 1999 -- OBIT-BRESSON-B&AMP;W-2 -- Robert
Bresson, the acclaimed French movie director whose best-known films
reflected a strongly esthetic and spiritual approach to cinema,
died Saturday. He was 98 and lived in Paris. He made his last film
in 1983 and had been unwell for some time. (The Museum of Modern
Art/Film Stills Archive)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT41) PALM SPRINGS -- Dec. 21, 1999 -- PALM-SPRINGS-LADN-2 --
The Korakia Pensione has drawn fawning praise from publications as
disparate as Los Angeles magazine and the London Sunday Times.
Lying a few blocks west of Palm Canyon Drive, the inn is actually
two properties, a 1920s Moroccan villa on one side of Patencio
Road, a Mediterranean villa on the other. Together, they're
composed of 20 rooms which range from $120 to $260 nightly. (Eric
Noland/Los Angeles Daily News)
