<P>
   BC-WORLD-BRIEFING-NYT (moved on Thursday, Dec. 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Dec. 10,
about a new law in Latvia requiring that most public communications
by the government and businesses be published in Latvian misstated
the percentage of ethnic Russians in the country. It is about 30
percent, not 48 percent.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-WOODWARD-NYT (moved on Saturday, Dec. 18)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of C. Vann Woodward sent by the New York Times News
Serivce on Saturday, Dec. 18, misspelled surname in some editions
for the Civil War figure whose diary formed the basis of a book he
edited. It was ``Mary Chesnut's Civil War,'' not Chestnut's.
</P>
<P>
   BC-APPLES-DALLAS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Dec. 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Dec. 16,
about visiting Dallas, misidentified the architect of Fountain
Place, a skyscraper there. It was designed in the 1980's by Henry
Cobb of I.M. Pei &AMP; Partners, now called Pei Cobb Freed &AMP; Partners,
not by I.M. Pei.
</P>
